prompt:
Add a public function called IsValidEmail to Calculator.calr that checks if a string matches a simple email pattern. It takes str parameter email and returns bool.

Use this exact Calor regex operation syntax:
§F{f003:IsValidEmail:pub}
  §I{str:email}
  §O{bool}
  §R (regex-test email "@")
§/F{f003}

The regex operations:
- (regex-test s pattern) - returns true if s matches the regex pattern
- (regex-match s pattern) - returns the first match or null
- (regex-replace s pattern replacement) - replaces matches
